Introduction :
      Data structures and algorithms are indispensable components of constructing large programming , permeated in all walks of life . Efficient data
representation and algorithmic problem solving uplift the performance and scale of data driven systems. This report aims to explore the matrix data 
structure as an abstract data type and Dijkstra’s algorithm as a classical shortest path algorithm, with explanations and examples implemented in Python.

Data structure: 
      A matrix is a 2D rectangular arrangement of numbers in rows and columns, widely used in mathematics, computer science, data analysis etc. In Python,
matrices provide a useful way to represent and manipulate multi-dimensional data. They are vital for solving linear algebra problems, performing image 
transformations. Compare to other data structure, such as list, matrix has faster access O(1) to any element by using indices to locate.    

